  "prompt": "What English dubbed anime websites and series are online, free and worth interest?",
  "response": "There are several online platforms where you can legally stream English dubbed anime for free. Here are a few notable websites and some popular series you might find interesting:\n\n1. **Crunchyroll**: While known primarily for subbed anime, Crunchyroll also offers a selection of dubbed anime available for free streaming with ads.\n   - **Popular Series**: \"Fullmetal Alchemist: Brotherhood\", \"Naruto\", \"Attack on Titan\".\n\n2. **Funimation**: Specializes in dubbed anime and offers ad-supported free streaming options.\n   - **Popular Series**: \"My Hero Academia\", \"Dragon Ball Super\", \"Fairy Tail\".\n\n3. **Tubi TV**: Offers a vast collection of free anime, including several dubbed options.\n   - **Popular Series**: \"Yu-Gi-Oh!\", \"Naruto\", \"One Punch Man\".\n\n4. **Hulu**: Offers a selection of dubbed anime with a free trial option.\n   - **Popular Series**: \"Sword Art Online\", \"Black Clover\", \"Bleach\".\n\n5. **RetroCrush**: Focuses on classic and nostalgic anime, often available in dubbed formats.\n   - **Popular Series**: \"Astro Boy\", \"Bubblegum Crisis\", \"Tokyo Godfathers\".\n\n6. **YouTube**: Some official channels upload full episodes of anime for free.\n   - **Example Channels**: Funimation's YouTube Channel.\n\nNote that availability can vary by region due to licensing agreements, and the selection of free content can change over time. Always ensure you are accessing content legally to support the creators and industry.",
